title: A different tone than the first, but great.
review: This is an amazing conclusion to the 2 part series.

title: An improvement over it's predecessor.
review: Cloverfield is one of my favorite movies, so the fact that this is better just shows how great it is.

title: Shyamalan's best.
review: Way ahead of its time and very underrated. This masterpiece still makes me excited and intrigued.

title: An intense action film.
review: This is easily the best one. I think the action is well made and its thought provoking. Well done for a YA adaptation.

title: A darkly hilarious, violent masterpiece.
review: So freakin good. This is definitley one of my favorites. Watching Brad Pitt scalp nazis is an entertaining sight.

title: I don't know what's wrong with me.
review: I just love this movie. It's funny I don't care. This is a movie from my childhood that I still love.

title: More than just a monster movie.
review: This movie had me mad with excitement. I was hooked from the opening scene. The effects are top notch even by today's standards and it's just an overall great movie.

title: I watched the extended version.
review: This is an intense and darkly funny film. It has plenty of great Tarantino dialogue and a hilarious ending.

title: Christopher Nolan is at his A Game with this one.
review: Chris Nolans best I think is Dunkirk, but this is still a masterpiece. I love it and I could watch it for days.

movie_title: Star Wars: Episode IX - The Rise of Skywalker
title: Cringe and just bad.
review: Don't watch this. Its like a transformers movie, just exsisting to sell toys.

title: One of the funniest movies ever.
review: Ive been seen terrible comedy movies. This movie was an exception. Watch it.

title: A great work from Edgar Wright.
review: This is a fun and energetic film about right and wrong. I recommend because its very funny and well made.

title: My favorite war film.
review: One of Chris Nolan's best. I can't even begin to describe how amazingly great it is. Just watch it yourself.

title: A slickly made movie.
review: This is a guilty pleasure that I enjoy. Its not great but it is watchable. Couldve used some non cgi magic tricks.

movie_title: Once Upon a Time... in Hollywood
title: Another banger from Tarantino.
review: This was a surpirisingly chill and hilarious film. Pretty good.

title: A masterpiece. Dang good.
review: I'm new to Tarantino. And he has not dissapointed. This is so good. This is a must watch.

title: LAZY!!!!!!
review: Boring, lazy, and filled with blandness, this movie is so bad, I cannot describe. I didnt even finish it. But the colorful setting gives it a 2 star rating. But dont waste your time here.

title: A masterpiece.
review: Eastwood gives a perfect performance as a racist old man who turns not racist. A truly astounding film.

title: An entertaining robot fighting movie.
review: This is by far the best one. What a solid action movie. Definitely watch this.

title: A great war film!!!
review: Shot beautifully and acted greatly. I enjoyed every second of this film. See it, you won't be disappointed.

title: A great film.
review: The action is over the top and hilarious, the villains have... character. No way. The movie could've just had the 'I'm evil' villains but they gave them complex backstories. What a triumph of a film. Can't wait to see the sequel.

title: A trash pile.
review: I can't sit through this plodding boring piece of garbage.

title: A hypnotic space trip.
review: I seriously thought this film was way to good for it's time. I mean 1968? Dang. Nice effects. Anyway 10/10, great film.

title: I came in expecting trash, I was wrong.
review: Holy cow this movie was so good. I haven't seen it for a while, but i remember it perfectly.

title: It's decent.
review: This movie is a good action thriller with terrific effects and stuntwork.

title: JJ Abrams is great at making movies.
review: I absolutely loved this film. Great cgi and suspense and references that aren't forced, this is definitely one of my favorites.

title: Beautifully animated but it still stinks.
review: Not quite sucks, but I think it is a boring plain dry movie for babies.

title: This is where the diarrhea kicked in.
review: One of the worst movies of all time. I don't ever want to watch this again. I liked it as a kid, but I was stupid back then.

title: One of the best films ever made.
review: Spielberg has never topped this. Jaws is a masterpiece that I could watch forever.

title: How was this that great?
review: A movie based on a Stephen King book could be great or awful. Thankfully this was amazing.

title: One of my favorite animated films.
review: Rango is a subversive take on a childrens animated film. Its very dark and thats what a childrens movie should be.

title: A banger from Stanley Kubrick.
review: The ending had me dang near tears. War is truly an awful endeavor and it's sad to see all those men who had gone through so much. Also the (SPOILER) Firing Squad scene is heart wrenchingly sad. But to leave on a positive note that battle sequence was epic as frick.

title: meh
review: I don't like this movie very much. It kind of sucks.

title: Not bad
review: Pretty entertaining and decent war movie. Not quite a FILM but a good movie. A popcorn action movie that does what it needs to do.

title: This movie sucked.
review: They had so much to live up to. I was expecting a good movie, and I did not get that. The villain sucked, the characters sucked and just the story sucked. Bad movie, do not watch unless your 5 or something.

title: The best action movie ever made.
review: I know Taken and The Dark Knight are contenders but this film wins it all. I have never experienced such a mind blowing spectacle. The use of barely any cgi was crazy. Truly a masterpiece.
